The paper presents a new model of plan recognition that is centered around a model of plan execution and uses probabilistic reasoning. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of plan recognition to build systems that will intelligently assist a user, which is a topic that falls under the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. The probabilistic nature of the model also suggests that it could be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the effect of context on plan adoption, which could be relevant to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on modeling the evolution of plan execution in situations where another agent intervenes suggests that it could be relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
